The [[President of the People's Republic of China|President]] is the second-highest ceremonial office under [[General Secretary of the Chinese Communist Party]] ([[paramount leader]]). However, the presidency has been held by the CCP general secretary since 1993. [[Term limit]] of the presidency was removed at the [[2018 National People's Congress]] that align the presidency with general secretary, which do not have term limits. [[Xi Jinping]] is expected to re-elected as the President in 2023.
